    "recap_headline": "Troy University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "HATTIESBURG, Miss.\n- Troy was unable to hold on to an early 4-0 lead in Sunday's rubber match against No. 12 Southern Miss, falling to the Golden Eagles 5-4 at Pete Taylor Park.\nThe Trojans (10-13, 3-3 SBC) started out strong in the first with a leadoff double by\nSteven Meier\nbefore\nAaron Piasecki\nknocked him in on a single. USM (19-5, 3-3 SBC) starter McCarty English was knocked out before recording an out in the third inning, loading the bases on a pair of singles by Meier and\nJosh Pyne\nand an HBP to Piasecki.\nUSM turned to one of its top bullpen arms, Camden Sunstrom, and the Trojans knocked in all three inherited runners on a two-run single by\nBlake Cavill\nand a fielder's choice from\nDrew Nelson\n. Sunstrom, however, was dominant over the next three innings, holding Troy scoreless, while JW Armistead (0.2 IP) and Camden Clark (2.1 IP) held Troy off the board in the final three frames.\nTroy starter\nTommy Egan\nstruck out six on the day and held USM to just a pair of runs through the first five innings on a third-inning Davis Gillespie homer, but the tides turned in the sixth. Meier lost a Gray Eubanks popup in the sun for a one-out double, and after a two-out RBI single by Seth Smith, Egan's day was done.\nBrock Tapper\nrelieved Egan, and an infield single from pinch hitter Ben Higdon that ticked off his glove kept the inning going. After back-to-back walks, USM tied the game before\nCooper Ellingworth\nentered to record the final out.\nSouthern Miss scored the game-winning run in the seventh on a sacrifice fly from Tucker Stockman after Matthew Russo led off with a walk and reached third on a wild pitch and a single. Ellingworth stranded the bases loaded in the eighth to give the Trojans one final shot, as Meier crashed into the centerfield wall for the inning-ending grab.\nMeier's spectacular catch came at a cost, as the centerfielder who already had two hits and a stolen base on the day exited the game due to injury.\nGavin Schrader\npinch hit for Meier against Clark in the ninth, and led off with a flyout. Piasecki reached on a two-out single, but Clark, who has yet to allow an earned run this season, fanned\nJimmy Janicki\nto end the ballgame.\nNotables\nTroy moves to 3-3 in Sun Belt Conference play following the series at Southern Miss, tying them for fourth through two weeks of league action.\nTroy recorded double-digit hits in all three games of a series for the first time this season. The Trojans had 14 on Friday, 12 on Saturday, and 11 on Sunday.\nTommy Egan\npitched 5.2 innings, his deepest start of the season.\nJosh Pyne\nextended his hitting streak to ten games. He's hitting .386 during that stretch.\nJimmy Janicki\nextended his hitting streak to seven games. He's hitting .452 during that stretch.\nSean Darnell\nextended his hitting streak to five games. He's hitting .421 during that stretch.\nQuotable\nHead Coach\nSkylar Meade\n\"I don't like losing to them by one run. We've had times when some of these games are there to be won, and there's been some misfortune. As soon as we hit that bus, we'll be moved on. I know where our team is. We'll have to get after it.\"\nNext Up\nTroy hosts Samford at Riddle-Pace Field on Tuesday for its first home midweek game. The Trojans then head down to Tallahassee for a game at Florida A&M on Wednesday before continuing on at Georgia Southern next weekend.",
